.:: Puzzle 4x4-Level-5-19::.
4 different brands of cigars are smoked: old-henry, bluemaster, aristoff, bongani
4 different games are played: go, whist, chess, mah-jongg
City: new-york, edinburgh, london, prague
The people use 4 different means of transport: roller, skateboard, snowmobile, taxi
 1. the person driving the skateboard is on the far left or far right##3
 2. the bluemaster-smoker is somewhere to the right of the bongani-smoker##5
 3. the person playing mah-jongg is on the left or right of the person playing go##3
 4. the person traveling to london is on the left or right of the bongani-smoker##3
 5. the person playing whist is between the person playing chess and the person traveling to prague##2
 6. the person traveling to london is in an odd position##4
 7. the person playing chess is the person traveling to edinburgh##1
 8. the person traveling to london is on the left of the person traveling to edinburgh##1
 9. the person driving the snowmobile is on the left or right of the person driving the skateboard##3
10. the person driving the roller is on the right of the person driving the taxi##1
11. the person driving the snowmobile is on the right of the aristoff-smoker##1
12. the person driving the taxi is on the right of the person playing go##1
13. the old-henry-smoker is somewhere to the right of the person traveling to london##5

.:: Answer ::.
|               |     1      |     2      |       3       |     4      |
| Cigar      | aristoff   | bongani      | bluemaster | old-henry     |
| Game           | mah-jongg   | go  | whist        | chess |
| City   | new-york     | prague     | london      | edinburgh   |
| Transport     | skateboard | snowmobile | taxi          | roller     |

